+    //
+    // Bug fix v2 (#keyboard-gap): two distinct stale states occur after the IME
+    // hides in immersive/kiosk mode:
+    //   (a) the keyboard-height bottom padding is left applied (resting inset
+    //       dispatch not delivered), and
+    //   (b) Chromium inside the WebView keeps its layout viewport sized to
+    //       screen-minus-keyboard, leaving the bottom of the page blank even
+    //       when padding is correct. A device rotation fixes it because rotation
+    //       forces onSizeChanged -> full Chromium relayout.
+    // Fix: reset padding explicitly on hide (v1), and additionally perform a
+    // one-frame 1px height "jiggle" on the content child when the IME
+    // transitions visible -> hidden. The jiggle triggers onSizeChanged in the
+    // WebView (rotation-equivalent) which forces Chromium to rebuild its
+    // viewport and fires a window resize event into the page.
